{{#layout-cell}}      <h3>Core Concepts</h3>
<p><strong>Templates:</strong> Control the structure of your Confluence page (`confluence-template.html`) and the embedded HTML macro (`macro-template.html`) using Handlebars.</p>
<p><strong>Asset Management:</strong> The tool automatically finds your build output (JS, CSS, images), uploads them as attachments, and injects the correct links into your macro template via `{{{scripts}}}` and `{{{styles}}}`.</p>
<p><strong>Macro Helpers:</strong> Use built-in Handlebars helpers (like <code>\{{#confluence-panel}}</code> or <code>\{{confluence-toc}}</code>) within your page template to generate rich Confluence content alongside your embedded application.</p>
<p><strong>Hierarchical Content:</strong> Create and maintain complex documentation structures with nested child pages, all managed through a single configuration file.</p>
<p><strong>Markdown Support:</strong> Write page templates in Markdown (`.md`) and they'll be automatically converted to Confluence XHTML while preserving Handlebars expressions.</p>
<h3>Classic Use Cases</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Interactive Dashboards:</strong> Embed real-time data visualizations (React, Vue, Preact, etc.).</li>
<li><strong>Training Materials:</strong> Create interactive documentation with live code examples.</li>
<li><strong>Internal Tools:</strong> Deploy team collaboration tools (planning poker, simple forms) directly in your workspace.</li>
<li><strong>Documentation Widgets:</strong> Enhance documentation with small, interactive components.</li>
</ul>
